#. <section class="sutta" id="an3.33"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an3.33:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 3"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 3"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.33:0.2"
msgid "4. Devadūtavagga"
msgstr "4. Messengers of the Gods"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an3.33:0.3"
msgid "33. Sāriputtasutta"
msgstr "33. With Sāriputta"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an3.33:1.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "Then Venerable Sāriputta went up to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side. The Buddha said to him:"

#. </p><p class="added">
msgctxt "an3.33:1.2"
msgid "“saṅkhittenapi kho ahaṃ, sāriputta, dhammaṃ deseyyaṃ;"
msgstr "“Maybe I’ll teach Dhamma in brief,"

msgctxt "an3.33:1.3"
msgid "vitthārenapi kho ahaṃ, sāriputta, dhammaṃ deseyyaṃ;"
msgstr "maybe in detail,"

msgctxt "an3.33:1.4"
msgid "saṅkhittavitthārenapi kho ahaṃ, sāriputta, dhammaṃ deseyyaṃ;"
msgstr "maybe both in brief and in detail."

msgctxt "an3.33:1.5"
msgid "aññātāro ca dullabhā”ti."
msgstr "But it’s hard to find anyone who understands.”"

#. </p><p class="added">
msgctxt "an3.33:1.6"
msgid "“Etassa, bhagavā, kālo, etassa, sugata, kālo "
msgstr "“Now is the time, Blessed One! Now is the time, Holy One! "

msgctxt "an3.33:1.7"
msgid "yaṃ bhagavā saṅkhittenapi dhammaṃ deseyya, vitthārenapi dhammaṃ deseyya, saṅkhittavitthārenapi dhammaṃ deseyya. "
msgstr "Let the Buddha teach Dhamma in brief, in detail, and both in brief and in detail. "

msgctxt "an3.33:1.8"
msgid "Bhavissanti dhammassa aññātāro”ti."
msgstr "There will be those who understand the teaching!”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an3.33:2.1"
msgid "“Tasmātiha, sāriputta, evaṃ sikkhitabbaṃ:"
msgstr "“So, Sāriputta, you should train like this:"

msgctxt "an3.33:2.2"
msgid "‘imasmiñca saviññāṇake kāye ahaṅkāramamaṅkāramānānusayā na bhavissanti, bahiddhā ca sabbanimittesu ahaṅkāramamaṅkāramānānusayā na bhavissanti, yañca cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ upasampajja viharato ahaṅkāramamaṅkāramānānusayā na honti tañca cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ upasampajja viharissāmā’ti."
msgstr "‘There’ll be no ego, possessiveness, or underlying tendency to conceit for this conscious body; and no ego, possessiveness, or underlying tendency to conceit for all external stimuli; and we’ll live having achieved the freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom where ego, possessiveness, and underlying tendency to conceit are no more.’"

msgctxt "an3.33:2.3"
msgid "Evañhi kho, sāriputta, sikkhitabbaṃ."
msgstr "That’s how you should train."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.134"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an3.33:3.1"
msgid "Yato ca kho, sāriputta, bhikkhuno imasmiñca saviññāṇake kāye ahaṅkāramamaṅkāramānānusayā na honti, bahiddhā ca sabbanimittesu ahaṅkāramamaṅkāramānānusayā na honti, yañca cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ upasampajja viharato ahaṅkāramamaṅkāramānānusayā na honti tañca cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ upasampajja viharati;"
msgstr "When a mendicant has no ego, possessiveness, or underlying tendency to conceit for this conscious body; and no ego, possessiveness, or underlying tendency to conceit for all external stimuli; and they live having attained the freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom where ego, possessiveness, and underlying tendency to conceit are no more—"

msgctxt "an3.33:3.2"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccati, sāriputta:"
msgstr "they’re called"

#. VAR: acchecchi → acchejji (s1-3, km, mr)
#. VAR: vivattayi → vāvattayi (bj, pts1) | vivaṭṭayi (s1-3)
msgctxt "an3.33:3.3"
msgid "‘bhikkhu acchecchi taṇhaṃ, vivattayi saṃyojanaṃ, sammā mānābhisamayā antamakāsi dukkhassa’."
msgstr "a mendicant who has cut off craving, untied the fetters, and by rightly comprehending conceit has made an end of suffering."

#. VAR: pārāyane → pārāyaṇe (bj)
msgctxt "an3.33:3.4"
msgid "Idañca pana metaṃ, sāriputta, sandhāya bhāsitaṃ pārāyane udayapañhe:"
msgstr "And Sāriputta, this is what I was referring to in ‘The Way to the Beyond’, in ‘The Questions of Udaya’ when I said:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an3.33:4.1"
msgid "‘Pahānaṃ kāmasaññānaṃ,"
msgstr "‘The abandoning of both"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.33:4.2"
msgid "domanassāna cūbhayaṃ;"
msgstr "sensual perceptions and aversion;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.33:4.3"
msgid "Thinassa ca panūdanaṃ,"
msgstr "the dispelling of dullness,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.33:4.4"
msgid "kukkuccānaṃ nivāraṇaṃ."
msgstr "and the cessation of remorse."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an3.33:5.1"
msgid "Upekkhāsatisaṃsuddhaṃ,"
msgstr "Pure equanimity and mindfulness,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.33:5.2"
msgid "dhammatakkapurejavaṃ;"
msgstr "preceded by investigation of principles—"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.33:5.3"
msgid "Aññāvimokkhaṃ pabrūmi,"
msgstr "this, I declare, is liberation by enlightenment,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.33:5.4"
msgid "avijjāya pabhedanan’”ti."
msgstr "with the smashing of ignorance.’”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an3.33:5.5"
msgid "Tatiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
